The founder and director-general of the Buhari Osinbajo youth movement (BOYM) and a chieftain of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Chief Kelvin Okolie has enjoined President Muhammadu Buhari to consider Dr Abubakar Alkali as his next chief of staff. Chief Okolie is confident that Dr Alkali currently stands out as a highly focused technocrat, academician and community leader who will successfully pilot the affairs of the office of the chief of staff to the President. Chief Okolie described the Sokoto-born Dr Alkali as a life-time Buhari loyalist and is confident that the former APC Diaspora chairman has the experience and patriotism to effectively pilot the affairs of the chief of staff’s office. Chief Okolie further expressed confidence that Dr Alkaii’s almost 30 years combined experience in both the public and private sectors including the academia will come handy for the office of chief of staff. Chief Okolie also stated that Dr Alkali will bring his wealth of experience to bear to the CoS office having worked in the public sector where he rose through the ranks to top management positions and also in the private sector as CEO in the petroleum sector. Chief Okolie further solicited the support and cooperation of all Nigerians particularly the youths in seeing that Dr Alkali is named as the next chief of staff to President Buhari. Chief Okolie is in no doubt that the appointment of Dr Alkali, would mean open doors towards the seat of power for Nigerian youths who are yearning to make meaningful contributions to the development of our dear country Nigeria. Chief Okolie condoled with President Buhari and late Mallam Abba Kyari’s family, while also prayinto God to grant eternal rest to the late chief of staff Mallam Abba Kyari who according to him is a patriotic Nigerian who discharged his duties diligently and died in service to his dear country Nigeria.